The paper discusses the application of Learning to Rank (LETOR) models in the context of e-commerce search, which falls under the Information Retrieval (IR) domain of computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of various machine learning techniques such as denoising auto-encoder and skip-gram based word embeddings, which are commonly used in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of product features, which may fall under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) or computer engineering (cs.CE).
